OL,6,FDue to austerity measures, the Labour-
OL,7,Frun council has already been forced to
OL,8,Fcut #369 million from its budgets
OL,9,Fsince 2010, but warns it must find
OL,10,Fanother #60 million worth of savings
OL,11,Fby 2027. This is due to rising costs
OL,12,Fand surging demand for social care
OL,13,Fservices.
OL,15,FNewcastle is not the first council to
OL,16,Fexperience financial difficulties.
OL,17,FAuthorities like Birmingham and
OL,18,FNottingham have already had to issue
OL,19,Fsection 114 notices, blocking any new
OL,20,Fspending commitments and effectively
OL,21,Fdeclaring bankruptcy.
